Class WorkOrderHandler

  • java.lang.Object
    • controller.WorkOrderHandler

  • public class WorkOrderHandler
extends java.lang.Object
    The Universale Integration Adapter integrates with third-party invoice systems and WorkOrderApp This application handles API requests and responses and maps the data with the data in WorkOrderApp.
    Since:
    2017-07-19
    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    Andres van Lummel

      • checkWorkOrderToken

        public static int checkWorkOrderToken(java.lang.String token,
                                      java.lang.String softwareName)
        Returns a code that will be used to check if the token is valid.

        This method sends a request to the WOA API with parameters: version, object, token and software_token the object in this case is employees.

        Parameters:
        token - softwareToken of the current user
        softwareName - the name of the third-party application
        Returns:
        the status code of the JSON reponse

      • setWorkorderStatus

        public static void setWorkorderStatus(java.lang.String id,
                                      java.lang.String workorderNr,
                                      java.lang.Boolean status,
                                      java.lang.String type,
                                      java.lang.String token,
                                      java.lang.String softwareName)
        This method sets the workorder status from complete to handled if parameter status is true
        Parameters:
        id - row_id of the current workorder
        workorderNr - number of the current workorder
        status - true if workorder status needs to be changed to handled
        type - the API method/call type
        token - softwareToken of the current user
        softwareName - the name of the third-party application

      • getTypeofwork

        public static java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.String> getTypeofwork(java.lang.String token,
                                                                  java.lang.String softwareName,
                                                                  java.lang.String type)
        This method returns all types of work or payment methods from the WOA API. Returns a standaard arraylist of types of work and payment methods if the API call returns an empty array
        Parameters:
        token - softwareToken of the current user
        softwareName - the name of the third-party application
        type - the API method/call type
        Returns:
        an arraylist with the types of work or payment methods

      • getData

        public static java.util.ArrayList<WorkOrder> getData(java.lang.String token,
                                                     java.lang.String type,
                                                     java.lang.String stat,
                                                     boolean updateStatus,
                                                     java.lang.String softwareName)
        This method sends a request with Returns all WorkOrders with status complete.
        Parameters:
        token - softwareToken of the current user
        type - the API method/call type
        stat - workorder status (klaargezet, opgehaald, compleet or afgehandeld)
        updateStatus - true if all workorder statusses need to be changed to afgehandeld
        softwareName - the name of the third-party application
        Returns:
        an arraylist with all WorkOrders
        See Also:
        WorkOrder

      • addData

        public static java.lang.Object addData(java.lang.String token,
                                       java.lang.Object array,
                                       java.lang.String type,
                                       java.lang.String softwareName,
                                       java.lang.String clientToken)
                                throws javax.servlet.ServletException,
                                       java.io.IOException
        This method sends a JSONObject to the WOA webservice JSONObjects that can be sent are: - Employees - Projects - Relations - Materials - Hourtypes - WorkOrders - WorkOrderStatus
        Parameters:
        token - softwareToken of the current user
        array - an ArrayList filled with information from one of the above objects
        type - the API method/call type
        softwareName - the name of the third-party application
        clientToken - optional clientToken
        Returns:
        an JSONObject with responseObject or an amount of workstatusses added to WOA
        Throws:
        javax.servlet.ServletException - ServletException
        java.io.IOException - IOException
